Equations: \[\begin{equation}
v_x = \frac{v_L + v_R}{2}
\end{equation}\] \[\begin{equation}
v_y = \frac{\ell_r}{L\cot\delta_l + \frac{W}{2}} \cdot v_x
\end{equation}\] \[\begin{equation}
\omega = \frac{v_R - v_L}{W}
\end{equation}\] where \(\ell_r\) is the distance from the rear axle to the center of mass, \(L\) is the wheelbase, and \(W\) is the track width.
